name: Aidan Bateman
pikehelp: Pike has helped me become a better adult. Being in this fraternity has helped me improve my social skills, my time management skills, and overall confidence.

name: Heath Brinkman
pikehelp: The friendships and opportunities that pike has given me have allowed me to create strong bonds with my fellow brothers and my school.

name: Drew Roberts
pikehelp: Pikes has given me a chance to extend my family and gain bonds that will last me the rest of my life. I never feel like I am alone because I know I will always have my brothers to have my back no matter what.

name: Julian Chhouy
pikehelp: Pike has helped me become a leader not only in the house but also in my community. My fraternity has helped me grow into an outgoing and outspoken person.

name: Josh Crawford
pikehelp: PIKE has helped me become more comfortable with myself and really learn who I was. Without PIKE, I would have never started powerlifting or known what I really wanted to do in life.

name: Steven Toro
pikehelp: Pike has taught me to be more outgoing and comfortable in my own skin, subsequently allowing me to make a lot of great connections with people I wouldn't have otherwise met. It's given me a group of friends I can rely on and confide with. Many times a freshman student can feel out of place in college since they leave so much behind, but I didn't have to deal with that because there was a brotherhood there for me anytime I needed them. Pike also has a large variety of young men with different backgrounds and cultures, so I had a good chance to learn a lot from them in that way as well.

name: Erian Gutierrez
pikehelp: Pike has helped me discover my full potential. Because of Pike my leadership skills and work ethic have skyrocketed, helping me both in school, work, and my personal life.

name: Andrew Janker
pikehelp: Pike has helped me target specific areas of my life in which I can improve myself. Through the help and support of the other members I have grown to be a more capable and well rounded individual.

name: Blaise Suhr
pikehelp: Pike has helped me to appreciate the differences and perspectives of others, regardless of their backgrounds. I can attest that Pike has taught me valuable lessons in humility, academic stability, and even has facilitated the spark in interest in my intended career path. Pondering on fraternity life is a personal experience that every college male should consider carefully, as I know Pike has transformed me into a much more versatile, proactive man.

name: Grant Peszynski
pikehelp: Pi Kappa Alpha has taught me balance: balance between school, my social life, and extracurricular activities. Pikes had also helped me meet more people and make life long connections.

name: Tan Chou
pikehelp: Pike has given me a sense of brotherhood that would be unacheivable elsewhere. I know that the men I call my brothers are the Most Best Men and that our bonds will last a lifetime.

name: Phil Fallah
pikehelp: Pike has taught me a lot about personal responsibility. Coming into college, I struggled a lot with time management but by surrounding myself with mature, smart men I learned how to prioritize between work, school, social events, and philanthropy.

name: Kevin Kiser
pikehelp: Pike gives me connections all over the world. One might just help me with my career someday.

name: Ransom Hatch
pikehelp: I've been able to serve in a multitude of positions that has helped sculpt me into the person and leader I want to be. I try to incorporate our ideals in my everyday life and I believe it helps me strive for greatness.

name: Josh Hartmann
pikehelp: Pike is largely responsible for my acquisition of excellent time management, confident social skills, weight-lifting knowledge, and leadership. By surrounding myself with an active and motivated group of alpha males I have made my life a mission to become the best version of myself.

name: Alek Peterson
pikehelp: Pike has connected me with a group of guys who care about bettering themselves, the community, and each other, and has presented me with many opportunities to improve on my weaknesses and support others as well.

name: Dominic Peretti
pikehelp: Pike has given me friends for life. Every moment I have been in the fraternity has made me into a better man, and it has shaped me into who I am today.

name: Matt Cohn
position: Alumni Relations Chair, PC '15 Vice President, New Member
pikehelp: Pike has made everyday of my college experience an Adventure. Pike has taught me things I could never learn in a classroom, while still motivating me to work hard at my studies. All in all, Pike has made me a greater person.

name: KJ Neaville
pikehelp: Pike has given me a network of friends and resources that I can rely on for anything. I have learned how to put aside differences with people and work towards mutual goals.

name: Joseph Watanabe-Gastel
pikehelp: Pike has helped me find the sense of belonging I missed from my sports teams. In addition, it has taught me time management skills and humility.

name: Jack Gularte
pikehelp: Pike has connected me to a group of people that have the same ideals and interests as I do. Pi Kappa Alpha has also given me a group of friends that I can trust and rely on which is something I've never really had before. I started my time at the University of Washington in the dorms and struggled to meet people that I could connect with. With Pike, I now have a small cornerstone at this massive University that I can call my own.

name: Henry Corrado
pikehelp: Allowed me to be more actively involved in our local community. Learn how to take initiative inside the house and in the classroom.

name: Alex Azera
pikehelp: My experiences at Pike have redefined the meaning of teamwork and personal responsibility. I have learned incredible time management and am always pushed to do and be better.

name: Emerson Matson
pikehelp: Pike has helped me realize that there is a lot more to college than just academics. We all come to college thinking that we will sit down and study all day in order to get through this experience and move onto the next part of our Lives. But this experience is more than just that, but a development process to help become better versions of ourselves in multiple facets of our Lives through SLAG. It has also helped me to inspire others to take on more involved roles in our academic community.

name: Kyle Dige
pikehelp: Pike has pushed me to reach for higher goals and attain them. It has also, prepared me for the real world by helping me get job applicable skills. Overall Pike has made me a more well rounded and better man.

name: Parker Shirreff
pikehelp: Pike has helped me by bringing me out of my comfort zone and teaching me to manage my time. I am much more sociable and organized with my time.

name: Cray Bryan
pikehelp: This organization has helped me in many aspects of my life. I have made some of my best friends through PIKE, and every member pushes me to be the best man I can be. This applies to pretty much every aspect of my life, whether it be the gym, sports, school, or social interactions.

name: Jeremy Kyle Russell
pikehelp: Pike has allowed me to stay on top of all aspects of my life. The expectation that is set by the chapter of its members is something that I see as a bare minimum for success.

name: Andy Mercado
career: Social Work/ Family and Youth Services
pikehelp: PIKE has given me the opportunity to develop my skills in leadership and communication. The fraternity has also allowed me to maintain a healthy lifestyle by having a strong focus on athletics in intramural competitions as well as philanthropy tournaments.

name: Mickey Kazmi
pikehelp: PIKE so far has developed a view and stance upon how I approach life obstacles and challenges. With a diversity of people within the organization, I really learned how to cope with differing opinions and lifestyles. I have much more to learn still as a new member, and I'm eagerly waiting to see what is to come.

name: Alexander Smout
pikehelp: Pike has helped me make social and professional connections that would have otherwise been impossible to establish. Through this house, I now have contacts and a network that will last me a lifetime.

name: Cody Tyo
career: Marketing/Public Relations Manager, Sports Journalist, or Government Employee
pikehelp: The friendships and connections that I have built in less than two years at PIKE have already improved my college experience more than I had ever imagined. It's provided me with some of the best times of my life and it has helped me become a more outgoing and well-rounded person. PIKE has helped me find my second home in Seattle.

name: Erik Callan Peterson
pikehelp: Pi Kappa Alpha has helped me with my social skills between people, and has allowed me to recognize my talents and apply them to the real world. Both Academically and Athletically, Pi Kappa Alpha has played a vital role in my college career. However most importantly, beyond any career or academic advantages I've acquired through this fraternity, I will have a group of brothers who will always be there for me until I die; and that is what brotherhood truly stands for.

name: Akash Puri
pikehelp: I have gained many friends and life experience. I know I will remain friends with a lot of people for the rest of my life.

name: Nicholas Montgomery
pikehelp: PIKE has helped me in all aspects of my life. From having motivated people always around me helping me succeed in both school and my personal life, to gaining school skills that will last me through the rest of my life. I give a lot of credit to PIKE for getting me to where I am now.
